race.comment: BABY HAZEL (4) improved last time out to grab third when she worked home well at the end of 1200m at Goulburn. Peaking now and can get the job done. ISHIKARI (10) returns and has been readied with a sharp trial win here. Is a winner over this trip. Expect to see her settle back early and be taking big strides late. FEIMAZUO (7) caught the eye fresh when working home strongly into the placings here. Will appreciate the added trip and is among the main chances. ZALE (3) didn't fire a shot last time against tougher opposition but will find this easier and is drawn to advantage. Expect him to roll forward and give himself every chance.
